ts=true`\n3. **Option C**: Stay in source directory and use: `meson /work/meson . -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true`\n\n**Additional Considerations:**\n1. Check if `/src/libcacard` contains `meson.build` file\n2. Verify meson version compatibility\n3. Ensure build directory `/work/meson` is created and empty\n4. The current script does: `rm -rf /work/meson && mkdir /work/meson` which is correct\n\n**Common Pitfalls:**\n1. Using old meson syntax with new meson versions\n2. Not specifying source directory when not in source directory\n3. Build directory containing existing meson build files\n4. Missing `meson.build` in source directory\n\n**Recommended Fix Strategy:**\nModify the build.sh script to use the correct meson command syntax. The simplest fix is to change:\n```bash\nmeson /work/meson -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true\n```\nto:\n```bash\nmeson setup /work/meson . -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true\n```\nor (if staying in `/src/libcacard` directory):\n```bash\nmeson /work/meson . -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true\n```\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 1] Build failed due to incorrect meson command syntax. The command \'meson /work/meson\' is treating /work/meson as source directory instead of build directory. Meson expects source directory first, then build directory. The correct syntax should be \'meson setup /work/meson\' or \'meson /work/meson .\' (with source directory specified). This is a configuration error that regressed from the original linker error.\n- [Attempt 2] Build failed due to shell variable execution order issue. The fix introduced \'$NSS_NSPR_PATH/dist/Debug/lib/libgcm-aes-x86_c_lib.a\' in the LIBS variable, but NSS_NSPR_PATH is defined later in the script with \'export NSS_NSPR_PATH=$(realpath $SRC/nss-nspr/)\'. Shell scripts execute sequentially, so variables must be defined before use. The NSS build completed successfully (881/881 steps), showing progress on the dependency build, but the script execution order needs fixing.\n- [Attempt 1] Initial build shows successful NSS/NSPr compilation but fails at meson configuration stage. The meson command syntax is incorrect: it\'s trying to use \'/work/meson\' as source directory instead of build directory. The correct syntax should specify source directory (/src/libcacard) and build directory (/work/meson) separately. This is a configuration error in the build script.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2020 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:5b4a8d18f9a854c128279c66c609f4f9c8dc29da9681ec1ecb98c5c1bb7f98e6\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y pkg-config libglib2.0-dev gyp libsqlite3-dev mercurial python3-pip python\n# Because Ubuntu has really ancient meson out there\nRUN pip3 install meson ninja\n\nRUN git clone  --single-branch --branch master https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard.git libcacard\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/nss-dev/nss.git nss\nRUN hg clone https://hg.mozilla.org/projects/nspr\n\nWORKDIR libcacard\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2020 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\n# Compile NSS\nmkdir $SRC/nss-nspr\nmv $SRC/nss $SRC/nss-nspr/\nmv $SRC/nspr $SRC/nss-nspr/\ncd $SRC/nss-nspr/\n# We do not need NSS to be built with address sanitizer\nCFLAGS="" CXXFLAGS="" nss/build.sh --static --disable-tests\n\n# Create a package config for NSS\ncp dist/Debug/lib/pkgconfig/{nspr,nss}.pc\nsed -i "s/Debug//g" dist/Debug/lib/pkgconfig/nss.pc\nsed -i "s/\\/lib/\\/lib\\/Debug/g" dist/Debug/lib/pkgconfig/nss.pc\nsed -i "s/include\\/nspr/public\\/nss/g" dist/Debug/lib/pkgconfig/nss.pc\nsed -i "s/NSPR/NSS/g" dist/Debug/lib/pkgconfig/nss.pc\nLIBS="-lssl -lsmime -lnssdev -lnss_static -lpk11wrap_static -lcryptohi"\nLIBS="$LIBS -lcerthi -lcertdb -lnssb -lnssutil -lnsspki -ldl -lm -lsqlite"\nLIBS="$LIBS -lsoftokn_static -lsha-x86_c_lib -lfreebl_static"\nLIBS="$LIBS -lgcm-aes-x86_c_lib -lhw-acc-crypto-avx -lhw-acc-crypto-avx2"\nsed -i "s/Libs:.*/Libs: -L\\${libdir} $LIBS/g" dist/Debug/lib/pkgconfig/nss.pc\necho "Requires: nspr" >> dist/Debug/lib/pkgconfig/nss.pc\n\nexport NSS_NSPR_PATH=$(realpath $SRC/nss-nspr/)\nexport PKG_CONFIG_PATH=$NSS_NSPR_PATH/dist/Debug/lib/pkgconfig\nexport LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$NSS_NSPR_PATH/dist/Debug/lib\n\n# compile libcacard\nBUILD=$WORK/meson\nrm -rf $BUILD\nmkdir $BUILD\n\ncd $SRC/libcacard\n# Drop the tests as they are not needed and require too much dependencies\nmeson $BUILD -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true\nninja -C $BUILD\n\n# We need nss db to work\ncp -r tests/db $OUT/\n\necho "XXXXXXXX" > $WORK/testinput\n\nfuzzers=$(find $BUILD/fuzz/ -executable -type f)\nfor f in $fuzzers; do\n\tfuzzer=$(basename $f)\n\tcp $f $OUT/\n\t# Check if it runs at least in build image\n\t$OUT/$fuzzer $WORK/testinput\n\t#zip -j $OUT/${fuzzer}_seed_corpus.zip fuzz/corpora/${fuzzer}/*\ndone\n\nrm $WORK/testinput\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nhomepage: "https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard"\nlanguage: c\nprimary_contact: "jjelen@redhat.com"\nauto_ccs:\n - "jakuje@gmail.com"\nsanitizers:\n - address\n - undefined\nmain_repo: \'https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/spice/libcacard.git\'\n\nfuzzing_engines:\n  - afl\n  - honggfuzz\n  - libfuzzer\n\n\n\n--- Project File Tree (Shallow View) ---\n📁 libcacard\n├── 📄 COPYING\n├── 📄 Makefile\n├── 📁 automation\n├── 📄 build.sh\n├── 📁 cmd\n├── 📁 coreconf\n├── 📁 cpputil\n├── 📁 doc\n├── 📄 exports.gyp\n├── 📁 fuzz\n├── 📁 gtests\n├── 📄 help.txt\n├── 📁 lib\n├── 📄 mach\n├── 📄 manifest.mn\n├── 📁 nss-tool\n├── 📄 nss.gyp\n├── 📁 pkg\n├── 📄 readme.md\n├── 📁 taskcluster\n├── 📁 tests\n└── 📄 trademarks.txt\n\n--- Recent Commit Changes ---\nNo relevant commit found.\n\n--- Fuzz Build Log (Last 500 lines) ---\n[644/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.rsa_blind.o\x1b[K\n[645/881] CXX obj/cpputil/cpputil.dummy_io_fwd.o\x1b[K\n[645/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.rsapkcs.o\x1b[K\n[646/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/mpi/freeblpriv3.mpprime.o\x1b[K\n[646/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.sha_fast.o\x1b[K\n[647/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/mpi/freeblpriv3.mplogic.o\x1b[K\n[647/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.shvfy.o\x1b[K\n[648/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.rawhash.o\x1b[K\n[648/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.sysrand.o\x1b[K\n[649/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.rsa_blind.o\x1b[K\n[649/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.tlsprfalg.o\x1b[K\n[650/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/mpi/freeblpriv3.mpmontg.o\x1b[K\n[650/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/freeblpriv3.secmpi.o\x1b[K\n[651/881] CXX obj/cpputil/cpputil.databuffer.o\x1b[K\n[651/881] CC obj/lib/freebl/verified/freeblpriv3