uld be `/src/libcacard`\n4. **Path Resolution**: Using `.` might cause issues in container environments; absolute paths are safer\n\n**Root Cause Hypothesis:**\nThe meson version in the Docker container is modern (≥ 0.60.0) and:\n1. Interprets `meson /work/meson .` as ambiguous\n2. May be parsing arguments differently than expected\n3. Requires explicit `setup` subcommand for clarity\n\n**Solution Patterns:**\nBased on the warning message and error pattern, the fix should use `meson setup` syntax:\n\n**Option 1 (Recommended)**: `meson setup /work/meson . -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true`\n- Uses `setup` subcommand as warned\n- Keeps current directory context (`.` = `/src/libcacard`)\n- Follows modern meson best practices\n\n**Option 2 (Alternative)**: `meson /work/meson /src/libcacard -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true`\n- Uses absolute path for source directory\n- Avoids `.` resolution issues\n- Still uses deprecated syntax but might work\n\n**Option 3 (Conservative)**: `meson setup /work/meson /src/libcacard -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true`\n- Uses `setup` subcommand + absolute path\n- Most explicit and clear\n- Should work with all meson versions\n\n**Additional Verification Steps:**\n1. Check if `/src/libcacard` contains `meson.build` file\n2. Verify meson version in container: `meson --version`\n3. Ensure build directory `/work/meson` is empty (script does `rm -rf $BUILD && mkdir $BUILD`)\n\n**Common Pitfalls to Avoid:**\n1. **Shell variable order**: Ensure `$BUILD` is defined before use (it is: `BUILD=$WORK/meson`)\n2. **Path existence**: Verify source directory exists and has `meson.build`\n3. **Permission issues**: Build directory should be writable\n4. **Environment variables**: PKG_CONFIG_PATH and LD_LIBRARY_PATH are set correctly for NSS dependencies\n\n**Implementation Strategy:**\nModify the build.sh script to use `meson setup` syntax. The minimal change is:\n```bash\n# Current (failing):\nmeson $BUILD . -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true\n\n# Fixed (recommended):\nmeson setup $BUILD . -Ddefault_library=static -Ddisable_tests=true\n```\n\n**Why This Should Work:**\n1. Addresses the explicit warning about deprecated syntax\n2. Uses modern meson `setup` subcommand\n3. Maintains same directory context (already in `/src/libcacard`)\n4. Follows meson\'s own recommendation from the warning message\n\n**Fallback Considerations:**\nIf `meson setup` doesn\'t work, try:\n1. Absolute path: `meson $BUILD /src/libcacard`\n2. Check meson version and adjust syntax accordingly\n3. Verify `meson.build` file exists in source directory\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 2] Build failed due to shell variable execution order issue. The fix introduced \'$NSS_NSPR_PATH/dist/Debug/lib/libgcm-aes-x86_c_lib.a\' in the LIBS variable, but NSS_NSPR_PATH is defined later in the script with \'export NSS_NSPR_PATH=$(realpath $SRC/nss-nspr/)\'. Shell scripts execute sequentially, so variables must be defined before use. The NSS build completed successfully (881/881 steps), showing progress on the dependency build, but the script execution order needs fixing.\n- [Attempt 1] Initial build shows successful NSS/NSPr compilation but fails at meson configuration stage. The meson command syntax is incorrect: it\'s trying to use \'/work/meson\' as source directory instead of build directory. The correct syntax should specify source directory (/src/libcacard) and build directory (/work/meson) separately. This is a configuration error in the build script.\n- [Attempt 2] The fix added \'.\' as source directory to meson command, but error persists. Meson interprets \'/work/meson\' as source directory and \'.\' as build directory, which is backwards from intended. The warning suggests using \'meson setup\' syntax. Two possibilities: 1) Source directory \'/src/libcacard\' lacks meson.build file, or 2) Meson version requires \'meson setup\' syntax. Need to verify if meson.build exists and try